resharedPost.text:
Arini (YC W24) is an AI receptionist for dental clinics that answers phone calls, and schedules appointments. 

Today's dental front desks are often stretched too thin, spending most of their time on the phone, yet still missing 35% of calls. Missed calls = missed revenue. Arini answers 100% of calls, 24/7.

Founders Abdulrahman Jamjoom and Rami Rustom met in high school in Jordan and co-founded a startup together two years ago. Computer science grads from Harvard and MIT respectively, they eventually worked together at Threads, an enterprise communication tool, where they led the AI team automating customer support, document feedback, notification triaging, and more.

After going door-to-door to dentists, shadowing them, and directly observing the challenges they encountered, they learned that the front desk was a critical bottleneck in increasing bookings, despite dentists in the US spending $7 billion annually on front desk staffing.

With Arini, they're helping practices increase revenue by booking more appointments, while also helping them reduce their operating costs.

Learn more at https://lnkd.in/gVQ65Ead and sign up for a demo at https://www.arini.ai.

Congrats Abdul and Rami on the launch!

data.text: Excited to share what I've been working on with Abdulrahman Jamjoom. Tell your dentist to sign up at https://arini.ai!

Introducing Tailor, customizable AI stitched into threads. 

The wave of consumer AI is some of the most magical tech we've tinkered with in some time. LLMs have made massive leaps in knowledge generation. With Threads being where teams communicate daily, we couldn't resist dreaming about the ways work will change moving forward.

For it to reach its potential, we knew it had to be so much more than putting a GPT endpoint in our various text boxes. We wanted to have the AI stitched into the fabric of Threads (ü•Å). 

After thinking through some new design paradigms, weeks of prompt writing, and working with early testers‚Äîwe‚Äôre excited to share the first 4 T(ai)lor-enabled behaviors already being rolled out to active members on Threads.

To see them in action, check out our announcement thread at https://lnkd.in/gnUwkS9x or threads.com/ai. 

Too many people to tag but shout-out to Abdulrahman, Rami, and Mehdi for bringing this to life, Mark for his leadership in the space, Tim & Rosalee for the amazing brand direction, Christopher for the unbelievable new UI flows that really help Tailor fit in, and for the rest of the Threads team for helping us polish, iterate, and refine our thinking. 

The only thing cooler than all of the AI developments happening right now are the team members I get to work with.

Kalshi is a platform where people can bet on anything. The markets proposed can be on topics like ‚ÄúWill Brexit happen by the end of the month?‚Äù or ‚ÄúWill Lionel Messi be the top scorer in the league this year?‚Äù. Kalshi is not the regular sports book or casino: people do not bet against the house, they bet (or trade) against each other with the odds they agree to. The power of the platform resides in its ability to gauge the ‚Äúwisdom of the crowds‚Äù on virtually any topic: in a way, it is a generalization of the stock market.

Website: http://www.kalshi.com/

SciTech is the annual conference organized by the MIT Arab Student Organization to expose, and engage with, the growing technological and scientific innovation in the MENA region.

The conference will be hosted at the MIT Samberg Conference Center on April 19-21. You can find more information (book your tickets!) on our website: http://scitech.mit.edu

Stay tuned as we release this year's speakers every week!

-----------------------------

Ola Doudin is cofounder of BitOasis, a bitcoin consumer wallet and instant exchange focused on cash-based emerging markets. BitOasis aims to change the way people transact and send money by making it easy and secure to use bitcoin. Ola is also co-founder of Yellow, a bitcoin payment processor, and currently serves as an advisor. She holds a BEng in Electronic Engineering from University of Birmingham and previously worked in IT Advisory for financial institutions at Ernst & Young London.

Book your tickets now to hear Ola speak at SciTech 2019. See you in April!

For the first time ever, the MIT SciTech 2019 Conference is introducing the SciTech IDEAthon Competition!

The theme of this year's conference is "Envisioning the Future: Cities of MENA," with a focus on the future of Energy, Infrastructure, and Innovation in cities across the MENA region.

If you are interested in solving problems in cities in the MENA region, then join the IDEAthon competition, and pitch your solution in front of our world-renowned judges for a chance to win!
We are looking for:
- students
- engineers
- designers
- innovators
to join us in coming up with the boldest and most impactful ideas to change the cities of the MENA region.

The IDEAthon is part of the larger SciTech Conference - you can choose to participate in the conference, the IDEAthon, or both.

Ticket sales will begin soon! So stay tuned!

For questions, feel free to reach out to scitech@mit.edu
